 />"},{"pid":"6d0d25f0ece974acac528c6236eccef8b8ba0e51","tid":2036292,"uid":64694,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":3,"replyTime":"2020-05-26T11:29:50.000Z","msg":"我覺得我做grammar exercise嘅時候係拎到啲concept，知道明白個概念，但一到同人講嘢就load唔到出嚟咁<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"baff8dde1bbea3b9a36c303c21852df9df2cf6dc","tid":2036292,"uid":64918,"like":10,"dislike":0,"score":10,"quote":{"pid":"dbcb5a9e49dd69e83d543f19845a9779d1654505","tid":2036292,"uid":64694,"like":0,"dislike":2,"score":-2,"quote":{"pid":"609732bd67842902864bfe1fd04131ee508829b6","tid":2036292,"uid":64918,"like":8,"dislike":0,"score":8,"quote":{"pid":"25cf66b424fd57a9e2f4ba38fc5558de6e3ba737","tid":2036292,"uid":64694,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-05-26T11:15:03.000Z","msg":"即係好似平時做grammar exercise嘅時候冇咩問題，答到晒啲問題，啲vocab fill in the blank都冇咩問題，但係一到同人講嘢就一片空白唔記得晒啲嘢講唔撚到噏唔到出嚟？<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-05-26T11:17:07.000Z","msg":"純粹訓練得少姐....... <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-05-26T11:23:19.000Z","msg":"咁做嗰啲exercise其實有冇作用？定係剩係對作文同閱讀有作用，對說話嘅作用較低？可唔可以咁講？<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-05-26T11:35:39.000Z","msg":"每個人一開始都會有呢種經歷, 你隻隻字都聽得明佢講啲乜嘢, 但係你就係唔識點開口. <br />\n<br />\n書寫同講係完全兩樣野,  ( 至少以前係.... 互聯網時代你發覺好多書寫都已經變咗做口語 ) <br />\n<br />\n最主要嘅原因係你冇其他參考, 書寫就已經反而做過好多次你知道點樣寫. 但係對話就因為你少經驗.  ( 大把鬼佬識講英文, 你叫佢寫佢都未必寫得叻... ) <br />\n<br />\n最簡單嘅方法就係睇多啲 外國 影片.  揀一啲自己有興趣嘅 Topic, 車又好, 化妝又好, ( 即係假設你係女 ), 科技又好, 甚至乎時裝雜誌乜都好. 聽多啲佢哋講英文你就會開始識得點樣用."},{"pid":"265605ef348678a74437761b93c316297bd6eddf","tid":2036292,"uid":252806,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"6d0d25f0ece974acac528c6236eccef8b8ba0e51","tid":2036292,"uid":64694,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":3,"replyTime":"2020-05-26T11:29:50.000Z","msg":"我覺得我做grammar exercise嘅時候係拎到啲concept，知道明白個概念，但一到同人講嘢就load唔到出嚟咁<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-05-26T11:36:45.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/tongue.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"28a9c4a2a2a4c669537fdbda48635e9d5ad6305a","tid":2036292,"uid":64918,"like":1,"dislike":3,"score":-2,"quote":{"pid":"6d0d25f0ece974acac528c6236eccef8b8ba0e51","tid":2036292,"uid":64694,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":3,"replyTime":"2020-05-26T11:29:50.000Z","msg":"我覺得我做grammar exercise嘅時候係拎到啲concept，知道明白個概念，但一到同人講嘢就load唔到出嚟咁<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-05-26T11:38:56.000Z","msg":"任何一種語言, 最大忌 就係要覺得自己講得啱. <br />\n<br />\n我同你講有陣時鬼佬講英文 Gramma 都有時候會錯 . ( 但係佢哋通常會自己糾正自己 ) <br />\n<br />\n所以你講嘢嘅時候其實係唔太需要理 Gramma, 講咗先, 錯咗之後下次再改.<br />\n<br />\n下下都諗自己一定要啱先講出嚟, 諗到嗰陣時就唔係叫對話啦 . 訓練得多你自己講完之後都會知道自己嗰句 Gramma 係錯. 之後慢慢糾正自己就得."},{"pid":"5df27e5978965ca268f6b3abd68a0571b82a9e44","tid":2036292,"uid":355064,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-05-26T11:40:02.000Z","msg":"我反而寫有問題<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"88e6da6d282ebcdb80da4593dd4fcd2de6c6f7c0","tid":2036292,"uid":64694,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"quote":{"pid":"265605ef348678a74437761b93c316297bd6eddf","tid":2036292,"uid":252806,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"6d0d25f0ece974acac528c6236eccef8b8ba0e51","tid":2036292,"uid":64694,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":3,"replyTime":"2020-05-26T11:29:50.000Z","msg":"我覺得我做grammar exercise嘅時候係拎到啲concept，知道明白個概念，但一到同人講嘢就load唔到出嚟咁<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2020-05-26T11:36:45.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/tongue.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-05-26T11:41:07.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://na.cx/i/NcKy7tY.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fna.cx%2Fi%2FNcKy7tY.jpg&h=c5323cc4&s={SIZE}\" 